*Slavs are the largest Indo-European ethno-linguistic group in Europe.* They inhabit Central Europe, Eastern Europe, Southeast Europe, North Asia and Central Asia.
Slavs are the largest Indo-European ethno-linguistic group in Europe. *They inhabit Central Europe, Eastern Europe, Southeast Europe, North Asia and Central Asia.* Slavs speak Indo-European Slavic languages and share, to varying degrees, some cultural traits and historical backgrounds.
They inhabit Central Europe, Eastern Europe, Southeast Europe, North Asia and Central Asia. *Slavs speak Indo-European Slavic languages and share, to varying degrees, some cultural traits and historical backgrounds.* From the early 6th century they spread to inhabit most of Central and Eastern Europe and Southeast Europe, whilst Slavic mercenaries fighting for the Byzantines and Arabs settled Asia Minor and even as far as Syria.
